MAX_CONTRIBUTION().notice: Max total contribution allowed, calculated from `TOKENS_PER_SLICE * type(uint32).max`

TOKENS_PER_SLICE().notice: Ratio between amount of tokens contributed and slices minted

claimSlices().notice: Allows a beneficiary to get any unclaimed slices to itself.

closeRound().notice: Close blunt round if target has been reached.  Consists in minting slices to blunt delegate, reconfiguring next FC and transferring project NFT to projectOwner. If called when totalContributions hasn't reached the target, disables payments and keeps full redemptions enabled.

didPay((address,uint256,uint256,(address.notice: Part of IJBPayDelegate, this function gets called when the project receives a payment.  It will update storage for the slices mint if conditions are met.

didRedeem((address,uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Part of IJBRedemptionDelegate, this function gets called when the beneficiary redeems tokens.  It will update storage for the slices mint if conditions are met.

directory().notice: The directory of terminals and controllers for projects.

isTargetReached().notice: Returns true if total contributions received surpass the round target.

payParams((address,address,(address,uint.notice: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource, this function gets called when the project receives a payment. It will set itself as the delegate to get a callback from the terminal.

queueNextPhase().notice: Configure next FC to have 0 duration in order for `closeRound` to have immediate effect

redeemParams((address,address,uint256,ui.notice: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource, this function gets called when a project's token holders redeem. It will return the standard properties.

setTokenMetadata(string,string).notice: Update token metadata related to the project

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Indicates if this contract adheres to the specified interface.

transferToken(address).notice: Transfers the entire balance of an ERC20 token from this contract to the slicer if the round  was closed successfully, otherwise the project owner. Acts as safeguard if ERC20 tokens are mistakenly sent to this address, preventing them to end up locked.

transferUnclaimedSlicesTo(address[]).notice: Transfer any unclaimed slices to `beneficiaries` in batch.
